##China's mask industry rises and falls in 17 years | prism

Micro-signal Lengjing

Feature Introduction, tencent news product column, "Prism" focus on financial in-depth reports.

By Wang Zhuoming, editor | Qingning Zhang
Production | prism tencent Xiaoman studio

Welcome to download tencent news APP for more quality information

January 31,21:00, Hubei Province new pneumonia prevention and Control Headquarters held the ninth press conference.

"Up to now, Wuhan still has structural problems such as insufficient supplies of masks, alcohol and disinfectant, " said Zhou Xianwang, deputy party secretary and Mayor of Wuhan

Five hours before the news conference, Private Hospitals in Wuhan Union Hospital and Wuhan were at loggerheads with the Wuhan Red Cross, which receives donations, over the distribution of masks.

At 15:00 on January 30, the Wuhan Union Hospital announced that it was running out of protective equipment again.

Not only the hospital lacks the mask, the domestic majority area all "a mask is difficult to obtain" .

Before the outbreak, China had a daily production capacity of 20m masks and was the world's largest producer and exporter, accounting for 50 per cent of global annual production. Nearly one thousand mask enterprises in the country, a mask to earn less than five percent of the money.

With the current demand boom, sudden change in the industry, mask manufacturers, upstream melt-blown cloth raw materials, then upstream polypropylene and other chemical manufacturers recovery.

SARS so far 17 years, this industrial chain several ups and downs.

China has an annual production of 4.5 billion masks

Is there a shortage of masks in China?

A dozen days ago, it was a question that could be answered almost without thinking, and things took a turn for the worse on the night of January 20th.

New cases began to increase in Wuhan on January 18, and confirmed cases appeared in Beijing and Guangdong on January 20. Zhong Nanshan was the first to shout out in the CCTV interview that night: "The current data shows that it [ COVID-19] is definitely passed on. "

One of the best ways to stop the virus from spreading from person to person is to wear a mask. "Mask" two words, destined to become this generation's most profound Spring Festival memory. Many people from New Year's Eve to the seventh day of the New Year, failed to snap up one.

Before the outbreak, there was no shortage of masks in China.

China's total production of face masks was 4.54 billion in 2018, FT reported, citing industry data. This data and the Ministry of Industry and Information Technology released the daily production capacity of the mask industry is basically consistent.

On January 29, an article was published on the website of the State Supervision and Administration Commission of the Central Commission for Discipline Inspection, "China is the world's largest producer and exporter of face masks, accounting for about 50 percent of the world's annual output. Our maximum production capacity is more than 20 million masks per day, " he said

As a general protective products, a large number of domestic enterprises can produce masks, in recent years the market supply is stable, a large number of production capacity for export, domestic demand is not high.

In 2016, the China Textile Trade Association had statistics that China's annual demand for various types of protective masks was around 800 million, divided into industrial protection, medical hygiene and civilian uses according to the purposes of the masks, the annual demand for masks for civilian use is about 200 million.

Since the outbreak, China has been able to produce as many as 20m masks a day, but that is only one-70th of the population. The purchasing power of 1.4 billion people makes any commodity instantly available.

Also, most disposable surgical masks need to be replaced every four hours. In Wuhan, the front line of the epidemic, mask consumption rate is far higher than other parts of the country. We need masks every day until this epidemic is over.

During the Spring Festival, a large number of mask enterprises stopped production.

"Now many enterprises are working overtime, and the output has now recovered to more than 8 million a day, " said Miao Wei, Minister of Industry and Information Technology, during a survey of mask production in Tianjin on Jan. 23. This is still some way from the peak output of more than 20 million birds.

Each enterprise still has part of the stock or goods in transit.

On January 27th steady medical, a public company, announced that it had shipped 108.9 m masks nationwide in the past month. People familiar with the matter told us that prudent medical urgently asked its sales staff to contact overseas buyers on New Year's Eve, delay delivery, recover orders for face masks, and sell them in large quantities at home.

So did Shandong Sanqi Healthcare, another of the nation's top-producing mask makers, which halted foreign trade orders and sent 2.4 million masks, more than 70,000 protective suits and 28,000 masks to Wuhan.

Foreign aid and emergency procurement also provide a large share of the domestic supply.

Data released by the General Administration of Customs on January 31 showed that from January 24 to 30, China imported 290 million yuan worth of epidemic prevention and control materials, including 56.228 million masks.

Surplus demand gap depends on the increase in output, the remaining enterprises to restart production as soon as possible, the upstream and downstream industrial chain coordinated combat.

The Enterprise to be bankrupt resumes production

The mask requirement is actually hierarchical.

On January 31, the COVID-19 issued a notice on issuing guidelines for the prevention and control of pneumonia among people at different risk of COVID-19 infection and guidelines for the use of pneumonia masks to prevent COVID-19 infection, it is a formal distinction between the various scenarios in which masks are used.

"notice" that KN95 / N95 and above Particle Protection Masks, protective effect is superior to medical surgical masks, disposable medical masks, field investigation, sampling and testing personnel recommended to use. It can also be worn by the public in highly populated or enclosed public places.

KN95 is the implementation of GB2626-2006 protective masks, N95 is in line with the National Center for Disease Control and Occupational Safety and health (NOISH) standard mask, both filter particulate levels above 95% .

In addition, the major hospitals are also in urgent need of medical protective masks according to Gb19083-2010, for non-intensive contact health care workers and the general public, this level of masks enough.

As a result of information collection channel's restriction, the Ministry of Industry and Information Technology has not counted to each level mask production enterprise quantity temporarily. According to Huanqiu, 16,625 companies in China operate in a range that includes respirators and respirators.

However, the N95 mask, due to the need to obtain United States certification, so have the production of qualified enterprises less.

The NOISH website lists all approved mask manufacturers and approved models, a cursory search can find: Hubei Xiantao, Qingdao, Rizhao, Jiangsu Suzhou, Guangdong Sihui, Shanghai and other provinces and cities distributed a large number of N95 mask manufacturers.

The vast majority of enterprises can only produce medical masks and ordinary masks.

Changyuan County, for example, is the capital of sanitary materials in China. In the mid-1970s, the area started from the production of cotton swabs, cotton balls, and gradually formed a low-value medical supplies industrial cluster.

Medical Mask, Pad Sheet, protective clothing are disposable protective supplies, the price is not high, the hospital unified into the low-value supplies sequence. Low-value consumables are less noticeable than higher-priced drugs and implantable devices, which were previously purchased by hospitals themselves.

Beginning in 2018, the national scope of low-value consumables into the trend of provincial-level centralized procurement, manufacturers are also facing the pressure of price cutting tenderers.

More are those ordinary masks for civilian use, which require enterprises to enter the market to digest. Environmental pollution worsened a few years ago, when ordinary masks that had been forgotten began to take the fast lane of "anti-smog" . Almost all masks for civilian use are produced in the direction of the anti-smog market.

With the significant improvement of the environment in the country in the past two years, the market demand for anti-haze concept masks was weakening until the recent outbreak.

On January 23rd Changyuan County launched a campaign to restart production at a local Eisai factory.

Changyuan City Market Supervision Bureau requirements, "not during the outbreak of hoarding goods, bid up prices, " and strict control of product quality, to ensure the safety and effectiveness of medical devices. In addition, enterprises are called on to give full play to their social responsibilities, overcome difficulties and organize production in preparation for war.

As in Changyuan County, more decentralized mask makers are starting up in the country, and while few can make the N95, production capacity for other standard masks is quickly recovering.

For example, a company in Guangzhou, which had lost money for many years, had started the write-off process in April 2019 and was now resuming production.

Downstream enthusiasm drives upstream recovery

Downstream enthusiasm drives upstream recovery.

N95 and KN95 have filter protection level mask, the core material is meltblown non-woven fabric. This is a non woven material, in the past the raw material medical gauze easy to lose yarn, can cause wound infections and even medical error, so now almost invisible gauze mask, almost all of them are made of non-woven fabrics with interlacing fibers and no threads.

According to the production process, non-woven fabrics can be divided into spunlace, heat treatment, wet process, spunbonded, melt-blown and so on. The melt-blown non-woven fabrics adopt unique technology, the fiber diameter can reach 0.5-10 microns, the superfine fiber makes the meltblown cloth have good air filtration and become the core filter material of the mask.

You Xiangyin, chairman of Jiangsu Liyang, which makes meltblown fabric, told us that one ton of meltblown fabric can produce one million surgical masks or 500,000 N95-level masks.

MIAOWEI survey before the Spring Festival, Tianjin teda Clean Materials Co. , Ltd. is one of the main manufacturers of meltblown cloth.

In May 2009, the company launched the world's first two-component melt-blown production line, a rapid increase from 3000 tons to 4500 tons a year. At present, teda clean's total meltblown capacity is 7,000 tons. As early as 2010, the national total production capacity of meltblown cloth has exceeded 58,000 tons.

In the middle of 2019 before the outbreak, the price of high-quality meltblown cloth was around 30,000 yuan per ton, while the average price was less than 20,000 yuan per ton.

Meltblown cloth and other non-woven fabric raw material is polypropylene, this chemical raw material mainly by petrochina, Sinopec, private enterprises accounted for about 30% .

In 2017, China's total polypropylene production capacity reached 23.5 million tons and consumption was 24.2 million tons, a small part of which came from imports.

The supply of raw materials is sufficient, and on January 31, Sinopec spokesman Lu Dapeng promised on behalf of Sinopec: "During the anti-epidemic period, Sinopec production of medical and health materials-related raw materials will not increase prices. "

However, there is a short-term imbalance between supply and demand for raw materials.

The original market price of the special filter material for masks is 18,000 yuan per ton, and now it is 29,000 yuan per ton, but it is still hard to get the goods, according to the mask manufacturer in Changyuan County.

Add to this the problem of labor costs during the Spring Festival, and many mask manufacturers in Sichuan, Guangdong and Shandong face the same dilemma as Changyuan in Henan: They are losing money in the near future.

"Most of the companies that produce face masks and protective clothing not only don't raise their prices to dealers, but also ask them not to raise their prices to hospitals, " confirmed the chairmen of two medical device companies in Changyuan, Henan Province, the factory price of medical masks is about 9 cents each, less than one dollar, and medical surgical masks are between 40 cents and 45 cents each.

Mask Industry is a long-term thin profit, oem profits more thin profit. A mask factory in Jiangyin, east China's Jiangsu Province, said it made 300m masks a year for Japanese contract workers at 2 cents apiece, earning less than 5 per cent each.

Many mask manufacturers have confirmed this profit figure to us.

In the terminal sales, although Ali, Jd.com and other e-commerce platforms ban mask price increases, but still can not prevent dealers through a variety of ways to increase retail prices. Indeed, as long as the increase is not too dramatic, more consumers agree with the urgency of the situation.

But in the national anti-epidemic background, ultra-high-priced retail masks are heavily fined, industrial chain any enterprise dare not malicious "fortune" .

Once the heavy wheels start turning, it's hard not to get a little carried away.

"Before 2003, there were not many mask manufacturers. During and after SARS, there was a round of blowout, and later some enterprises emerged because of the smog. Now the smog is not so serious, and some mask enterprises have been eliminated, " Liu Hongbin, director of the National Labor Protection Products Quality Supervision and Inspection Center (Wuhan) , told the China Times, "before this, domestic mask companies had a very poor life, or even serious overcapacity.

Since April 15,2009, when influenza a (H1N1) began to wreak havoc around the world, masks became popular, driving the price of meltblown cloth upstream skyrocketing from 20,000 yuan to 130,000 yuan per ton.

The outbreak, initially called "swine flu, " began in the United States, with China less affected and much of the mask demand coming from overseas. There is no market supervision, no price increase ban, according to their judgment on the market expansion of production capacity.

In 2009, the national meltblown cloth production capacity increased 41% , teda clean is then launched a new production line.

The H1N1 outbreak was largely under control in July of that year, and masks were sold overnight, shelving a production line that had cost just one million Renminbi. Many Chinese mask and non-woven fabric enterprises first taste of blind expansion.

Since then, there has been technological upgrading, the development of water seepage and sound-absorbing materials, into shoes and car interior, such as the melt-blown industry self-help. Until "Haze" becomes the key word, the mask is taken seriously again, the whole industry takes a breather.

As the smog dissipates, the medical control expense, the mask industry once again falls silent, the time is worth recently, a batch of small and medium-sized enterprises because of the loss-making production, the free donation, becomes the Chinese manufacturing industry "the retrograde person" .

"Most of the companies that produce face masks and protective clothing not only don't raise their prices to dealers, but also ask them not to raise their prices to hospitals, " confirmed the chairmen of two medical device companies in Changyuan, Henan Province, the factory price of medical masks is about 9 cents each, less than one dollar, and medical surgical masks are between 40 cents and 45 cents each.

Mask Industry is a long-term thin profit, oem profits more thin profit. A mask factory in Jiangyin, east China's Jiangsu Province, said it made 300m masks a year for Japanese contract workers at 2 cents apiece, earning less than 5 per cent each.

Many mask manufacturers have confirmed this profit figure to us.

In the terminal sales, although Ali, Jd.com and other e-commerce platforms ban mask price increases, but still can not prevent dealers through a variety of ways to increase retail prices. Indeed, as long as the increase is not too dramatic, more consumers agree with the urgency of the situation.

But in the national anti-epidemic background, ultra-high-priced retail masks are heavily fined, industrial chain any enterprise dare not malicious "fortune" .

Once the heavy wheels start turning, it's hard not to get a little carried away.

"Before 2003, there were not many mask manufacturers. During and after SARS, there was a round of blowout, and later some enterprises emerged because of the smog. Now the smog is not so serious, and some mask enterprises have been eliminated, " Liu Hongbin, director of the National Labor Protection Products Quality Supervision and Inspection Center (Wuhan) , told the China Times, "before this, domestic mask companies had a very poor life, or even serious overcapacity.

Since April 15,2009, when influenza a (H1N1) began to wreak havoc around the world, masks became popular, driving the price of meltblown cloth upstream skyrocketing from 20,000 yuan to 130,000 yuan per ton.

The outbreak, initially called "swine flu, " began in the United States, with China less affected and much of the mask demand coming from overseas. There is no market supervision, no price increase ban, according to their judgment on the market expansion of production capacity.

In 2009, the national meltblown cloth production capacity increased 41% , teda clean is then launched a new production line.

The H1N1 outbreak was largely under control in July of that year, and masks were sold overnight, shelving a production line that had cost just one million Renminbi. Many Chinese mask and non-woven fabric enterprises first taste of blind expansion.

Since then, there has been technological upgrading, the development of water seepage and sound-absorbing materials, into shoes and car interior, such as the melt-blown industry self-help. Until "Haze" becomes the key word, the mask is taken seriously again, the whole industry takes a breather.

As the smog dissipates, the medical control expense, the mask industry once again falls silent, the time is worth recently, a batch of small and medium-sized enterprises because of the loss-making production, the free donation, becomes the Chinese manufacturing industry "the retrograde person" .

Downstream enthusiasm drives upstream recovery.

N95 and KN95 have filter protection level mask, the core material is meltblown non-woven fabric. This is a non woven material, in the past the raw material medical gauze easy to lose yarn, can cause wound infections and even medical error, so now almost invisible gauze mask, almost all of them are made of non-woven fabrics with interlacing fibers and no threads.

According to the production process, non-woven fabrics can be divided into spunlace, heat treatment, wet process, spunbonded, melt-blown and so on. The melt-blown non-woven fabrics adopt unique technology, the fiber diameter can reach 0.5-10 microns, the superfine fiber makes the meltblown cloth have good air filtration and become the core filter material of the mask.

You Xiangyin, chairman of Jiangsu Liyang, which makes meltblown fabric, told us that one ton of meltblown fabric can produce one million surgical masks or 500,000 N95-level masks.

MIAOWEI survey before the Spring Festival, Tianjin teda Clean Materials Co. , Ltd. is one of the main manufacturers of meltblown cloth.

In May 2009, the company launched the world's first two-component melt-blown production line, a rapid increase from 3000 tons to 4500 tons a year. At present, teda clean's total meltblown capacity is 7,000 tons. As early as 2010, the national total production capacity of meltblown cloth has exceeded 58,000 tons.

In the middle of 2019 before the outbreak, the price of high-quality meltblown cloth was around 30,000 yuan per ton, while the average price was less than 20,000 yuan per ton.

Meltblown cloth and other non-woven fabric raw material is polypropylene, this chemical raw material mainly by petrochina, Sinopec, private enterprises accounted for about 30% .

In 2017, China's total polypropylene production capacity reached 23.5 million tons and consumption was 24.2 million tons, a small part of which came from imports.

The supply of raw materials is sufficient, and on January 31, Sinopec spokesman Lu Dapeng promised on behalf of Sinopec: "During the anti-epidemic period, Sinopec production of medical and health materials-related raw materials will not increase prices. "

However, there is a short-term imbalance between supply and demand for raw materials.

The original market price of the special filter material for masks is 18,000 yuan per ton, and now it is 29,000 yuan per ton, but it is still hard to get the goods, according to the mask manufacturer in Changyuan County.
